	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=127934><span id= >Dadalan</span></a><br><span id=notbold>10 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.60]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This is simply to call your pet to your side (like a point to point teleport, or the Mage Call of the Hero spell). This does not actually make a pet. And yes the Wizzy Familiar is considered a pet per say... i.e. you conjure him and your pet window says he's there, it's just that the command buttons are grayed out. Now although I think Alla's just added Cleric incorrectly as the picture doesn't say CLR... Clerics and wizards actually do both get pet's that will attack. However, you can't control them other then to send them to attack one single mob after which they poof, so you wouldn't have time to use this spell or any reason to for that matter. Though there is a way for them to stay alive... if you get hit by another mob while they are attacking the first and you keep your target on the 2nd mob that attacked you then when they are done with the first mob they will jump to the second. But that's hardly practical (and doesn't always work), and also these pet's only have 100hp so you can't use them without a meatshield on the mobs already. But Clerics get a Hammer that fly's at the mob and starts swinging, while Wizzy's get a big Sword that does the same. Basically it must be cast on each mob, so it really is more like a visible DoT then anything.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
