	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93826><span id=Guru>goukix</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>15 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I've never had Boo Boo Bear con that low. From asking lowbies to con him, the bear cons around level 29. It does hit consistently for 30 damage though and with that it is used mainly as:<br><br>1. A farming tool (eats green spiders easily)<br>2. An extra 500ish HP. The bear makes a good deterrent (meatshield) if you find yourself in a unexpected situation where a mob is beating you down. The bear's taunt is very potent and gives you enough time to cast Gate while 'Boo Boo takes one for the team.'<br>3. A conversation toy (ladies love the lil' bear)<br>4. Having fun with the newbies (in a twisted way). Get a hold of this item: <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=8933" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=8933</a> , go to GFay and tree-form up near one of the 3 lifts and park Boo Boo right near it. From there have Boo Boo 'talk' to the newbies that wander by. Tons of silly fun.<br><br>Boo Boo: &quot;Hail newbie_#077...I am Gobantik, the special quest-giving little bear and today I'm looking for some rusty weapons. If you find me a rusty weapon I can grant a special Spirit of Wolf upon you.&quot;<br><br>/ahem<br>Sorry, I got side-tracked.<br>As for the belt, a clicky Summon Companion spell on a WIS/INT +Mana +HP (as well as good AC) item is not bad for the classes that rely on pets to level. However, since I'm usually in one area (camp) the pet doesn't wander off at all nor do I have alot of running around to do. So in essence the SC effect is like sprinkles on an ice cream cone: very nice but not necessary.<br><br>/cynical opinion on<br>*I personally believe SOE created Summon Companion spell to deal with the horrible and awful pathing in some zones where pets decide to go astray even while you are spamming 'follow'.<br><br>You: &quot;Follow me.&quot;<br>Pet: &quot;Following you, Master.&quot;<br>You: Wait...why are you zig-zagging up that hill away from me?<br>Pet: Sorry Master, I have to pee...<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Jun 20 12:46:05 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
